reviews.text:
It's not bad at all for breakfast set  including hot drink.
The vermicelli in minced pork with chili and basil in soup $30 was not exactly Vietnamese in flavor but passable.
For inside YOHO mall that's very reasonable price.

Definitely one of the best in town, pho soup base is clear n tasty without much msg at all.  There is also enough beef in the noodles, v good value for money. A list for pho in HK, must try, though there is always a waiting line outside

Hey What’s up food hunters 😎wanna eat like a hongkie(local people) , today i went a Vietnam noodle place for lunch , i have order a bow of raw beef noodle & a bow of Pho mixed noodle & a shrimp rice paper roll & a vietnam drop coffee & a lemongrass soda , first both noodles are good, beefs are not too chewy and the soup is taste good also , viet coffee and lemongrass is good too i recommend lemongrass drink more then coffee , the shrimp rolls r great 👍🏻 it’s only HK$28 worth for the money , Overall - it is not a real real authentic vietnam restaurant but if u stop by and hungry go for it , place is clean and neat ⭐️⭐️⭐️out of 5 , its an open space and busy restaurant not a eat&chit chat place so eat and go , by the time i go there at 13:50 it still has a long queue u can see in my photos , i spend HK$204 decent 👍🏻see u guys on the next one , peace ✌🏻 -Detour Guide-
食物水準很好比起外面的越南菜館是勝了一籌可惜服務態度一般
每次都要排隊的越南河粉，牛肉湯很鮮甜，價錢也合理。

reviews.text: So many kind of shop.  All product are high quality.
it has good clothing items and also make up booths. They also have pop up shops sometimes

Mall 2 has sports shops such as gigasports with ok range of speed and arena brand swimming goggles and budget food options such as maccas and cafe de coral. To get there u have to walk through a ridiculous car park from yoho 1 if u come from mtr. U have to go up one level from mtr level to get there and u will most likely get lost even though it is simple layout. Cinema at one end of yoho 1 with yata.

result.name: 錦麗

reviews.text: 食物水準很好比起外面的越南菜館是勝了一籌可惜服務態度一般
每次都要排隊的越南河粉，牛肉湯很鮮甜，價錢也合理。

錦麗已經係本地出咗名嘅越南牛肉粉餐廳，差唔多間間分店去食都要排隊，呢間喺 YOHO II 嘅分店都唔例外，好在只係排咗十幾分鐘就有位; 由於地方細，所以單人或二人嚟食就經常要撘枱。食物主打係以牛肉為主嘅越南湯粉，加春卷、牛油鷄翼等大家都熟悉嘅越式小食。生牛肉粉最吸引嘅地方係鮮甜嘅湯底、河粉幼滑、牛肉薄又嫩，全部新鮮製造，係水準以上之作; 春卷新鮮熱辣炸起上，皮簿鬆脆，配河粉食真係一流。總括嚟講，呢度嘅食物好味又高水準，服務亦唔錯，只係地方淺窄，食完有趕頭趕命嘅感覺，但我仍然會繼續幫襯，非繁忙時段會食得舒服啲。😋

It's not bad at all for breakfast set  including hot drink.
The vermicelli in minced pork with chili and basil in soup $30 was not exactly Vietnamese in flavor but passable.
For inside YOHO mall that's very reasonable price.

一間價錢和味道可以的餐廳！
個別員工服務有待改善，日日都咁炆。
